Subject: [PATCH] [PATCH] set ip6 variable to ansible_default_ipv6.address use
 ansible_default_ipv6['address'] to set ip6 variable if available.  If ip6
 variable is already defined, then do nothing, that should ensure backwards
 compatibility and not break current logic.

---
 playbooks/internal_facts.yml | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/playbooks/internal_facts.yml b/playbooks/internal_facts.yml
index 5bb97f073..9a4d28296 100644
--- a/playbooks/internal_facts.yml
+++ b/playbooks/internal_facts.yml
@@ -30,6 +30,13 @@
         gather_subset: '!all,!min,network'
         filter: "ansible_*_ipv[46]*"
 
+    - name: Set ip6 variable
+      set_fact:
+        ip6: "{{ ansible_default_ipv6['address'] }}"
+      when:
+        - not ip6 is defined
+        - ansible_default_ipv6 is defined and ansible_default_ipv6 is mapping and ansible_default_ipv6.address is defined
+
     # filter match the following variables:
     # ansible_memtotal_mb
     # ansible_swaptotal_mb
